.TH "batadv_is_my_client" 9 "batadv_is_my_client" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_is_my_client \- check if a client is served by the local node
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_is_my_client
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "const u8 *addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "addr" 12
the mac address of the client to check
.IP "vid" 12
VLAN identifier
.SH "RETURN"
true if the client is served by this node, false otherwise.
